In this article, President Obama proclaims November 11, 2012, as Veterans Day and encourages all Americans to recognize and honor the valor and sacrifice of veterans. He acknowledges the contributions and sacrifices made by veterans throughout history, from the War of 1812 to the recent wars in Iraq and Afghanistan. The President emphasizes that the service of veterans is not limited to their time in the military, as many continue to serve their communities in various roles. He highlights the importance of fulfilling our responsibilities to veterans and providing them with the benefits and support they deserve. The article also mentions the legal public holiday established by Congress to honor veterans on November 11 each year. President Obama calls upon Federal, State, and local officials, as well as civic and fraternal organizations, places of worship, schools, and communities to participate in patriotic activities and ceremonies to commemorate Veterans Day.